PrecisOrder which provides for (a) the withdrawal of the entrustment conferred upon the CANADIAN NATIONAL RAILWAY COMPANY with respect to two parcels of land situate in the CITY of HALIFAX, Nova Scotia, the first parcel being situate on Kempt Road (15.14 acres), which was occupied under lease by Dominion Metals, and the other consisting of the Willow Park spur line right-of-way (10.97 acres); and (b) the sale of those same lands to the Canadian National Railway Company.
